snippet.description:
'I Touch Myself' Singer Dead at 53
22 Apr 2013 by Doug Fairall on Radar Online radaronline.com/2013/04/i-touch-myself-singer-dead-at-53/
Chrissy Amphlett, the raunchy lead singer of the Australian rock band Divinyls whose hit I Touch Myself brought her international fame in the early 1990s, has died at 53.
